sections.heading: to strike pleadings and papers from files; notice, when
sections.text: Motions to strike pleadings and papers from the files may be made with or without notice, as the court or judge shall direct.SourceR.S.1867, Code § 577, p. 495;R.S.1913, § 7729;C.S.1922, § 8673;C.S.1929, § 20-913;R.S.1943, § 25-913.AnnotationsM
